HEADWORD: Ploce
<hw>Plo"ce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/
complication, fr. <?/ to entwine.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A
figure in which a word is separated or repeated by way of emphasis, so
as not only to signify the individual thing denoted by it, but also its
peculiar attribute or quality; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧His <ex>wife</ex>'s a
<ex>wife</ex> indeed</as>.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

